The central competent authority shall establish the GHG Management Fund (Fund) from the following sources:
* Proceeds from allowances auctioned or sold pursuant to the foregoing Article;
* Fees collected pursuant to Article 21;
* Government grant via budget appropriation;
* Revenues collected under fines and penalties prescribed in the Act;
* Money received from persons, liable entities or organizations; and
* Other incomes.

The Fund shall serve the following purpose only for GHG emissions reductions and adaptation to climate change:
* Reduce GHG emissions;
* Inspect emission sources;
* Provide emission sources with assistance, subsidies and grants for voluntary efforts to
* Administrative affairs of holding accounts establishment in the Registry, auctions, sales
* Employ staff to carry out administrative services;
* Coordinate, plan and implement adaptation to climate change;
* Educate, promote, and award grants;
* Conduct international affairs;
* Carry out research and analysis.

